Project Overview

This project is part of my Data Analyst Bootcamp and focuses on building foundational skills in data visualisation using Tableau and Power BI.
The workbook introduces industry-standard visualisation tools and demonstrates how they are used to explore data,
identify patterns, and communicate insights effectively.

ðŸŽ¯ Project Intent
The main objectives of this project were to:
Understand what Tableau and Power BI are and how they are used in data analysis
Compare the benefits of visualisation tools over traditional spreadsheet analysis (e.g. Excel)
Learn how to import and prepare data for analysis
Understand data relationships and how they affect visual outputs
Learn the purpose and structure of dashboards for presenting insights

ðŸ›  Implementation Approach
The project was delivered through:
Hands-on practical labs
Step-by-step guided exercises
Concept explanations supported by real examples
Short quizzes and tasks to reinforce understanding
This practical approach helped translate theory into applied skills using Tableau and Power BI.

ðŸ“ˆ Impact & Skills Gained
By completing this project, I:
Gained confidence using Tableau and Power BI for data exploration
Developed an understanding of visual analytics workflows
Learned how dashboards support data-driven decision-making
Built foundational visualisation skills required for real-world data analysis
Progress and learning outcomes were measured through in-class mini-projects, labs, and quizzes,
ensuring both conceptual understanding and practical competence.

ðŸ’¡ Career Context
As a career changer into data analytics, this project represents an important milestone in
developing the ability to communicate insights visually, a key skill for data analyst roles.
